<h2>How to Analyze Keyword Competition</h2>
<p>Follow this process for every target keyword.</p>
<h3>Step 1: Check Keyword Difficulty</h3>
<p>Use your preferred tool to check KD. Record the score.</p>
<p><strong>Tools:</strong>
- Ahrefs Keyword Explorer
- Semrush Keyword Magic Tool
- Moz Keyword Explorer
- Ubersuggest
- Mangools KWFinder</p>
<h3>Step 2: Analyze the SERP</h3>
<p>Search the keyword in Google. Analyze the top 10 results manually.</p>
<p><strong>SERP analysis checklist:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Are results dominated by big brands (Amazon, Wikipedia, Forbes)?</li>
<li>[ ] Are there featured snippets?</li>
<li>[ ] Are there image or video results?</li>
<li>[ ] Are there local pack results?</li>
<li>[ ] Are there shopping results?</li>
<li>[ ] Are there People Also Ask boxes?</li>
<li>[ ] How many ads appear?</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Red flags (high competition):</strong>
- Top 3 results from DR 80+ sites
- Featured snippet from a major brand
- 4+ ads above organic results
- Wikipedia or government sites ranking</p>
<p><strong>Green flags (lower competition):</strong>
- Forums or Q&amp;A sites ranking (Reddit, Quora)
- Small blogs in the top 10
- Outdated content ranking
- Thin content ranking</p>
