<h2>Common Mistakes</h2>
<p><strong>Mistake 1: Relying solely on KD score.</strong> KD measures backlinks, not content quality. Always analyze the actual SERP.</p>
<p><strong>Mistake 2: Ignoring search intent.</strong> A keyword with low KD but mismatched intent is still hard to rank for.</p>
<p><strong>Mistake 3: Only targeting easy keywords.</strong> Easy keywords have low volume. Balance easy wins with higher-value targets.</p>
<p><strong>Mistake 4: Not analyzing content quality.</strong> A low KD keyword with excellent content from strong brands is still competitive.</p>
<p><strong>Mistake 5: Forgetting about SERP features.</strong> Featured snippets, local packs, and ads reduce organic click-through rates.</p>
